President Joe Biden addressed the United Auto Workers (UAW) union, expressing his support for unions and the middle class. He emphasized the importance of unions in building America and creating a strong middle class. Biden praised the UAW's history and its role in winning collective bargaining rights and improving workers' wages and benefits. He highlighted the union's recent victories in securing record wage increases and better working conditions for its members. The President also discussed his administration's efforts to invest in American manufacturing, particularly in the electric vehicle industry, and to create jobs for American workers. He emphasized his commitment to buying and building American products and called for a fair shot for working people in the country's economy. Biden thanked the UAW for its support and expressed his optimism for America's future.